 The South Africa Weather Service has warned of disruptive rain that could lead to flooding on the KZN South Coast. It said in a statement that the rain could lead toÂ  further damage to roads, bridges and properties, flooding of susceptible formal/informal settlements as well as mudslides on Saturday, over the southern interior and western parts of KZN. In Pietermaritzburg the maximum temperature is expected to reach 15 degrees while in Durban it will reach 18 degrees. 